==English== 

===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[altare]]''', ''altar'', probably related to '''[[adolere]]''', ''burn''; thus ''burning place'', influenced by a false connection with '''[[altus]]''', ''[[high]]''.

===Pronunciation===
====Homophones====
*[[alter]]

===Noun===
'''altar''', plural [[altars]]
# A table or similar flat-topped structure used for religious rites.

====Derived terms====
*[[altar boy]]

====Related terms====
*[[adolere]]
*[[ara]]

